A model of the BeiDou Satellite Navigation System is on display during the 20th China Beijing International High-tech Expo in June 2017. Photo: ICSome business runners approached by the Global Times reporter at the CSNC expressed their concerns over the escalating China-US trade war."BDS itself is entirely safe from the trade war," said Chen Yingdong, deputy head of the big data of the expert panel under the GNSS and LBS Association of China - a no-profit organization in global navigation satellite system application and location-based service.However, BDS application which is based on relevant software and hardware might be affected by US' unreasonable pressure on Chinese enterprises, he noted.According to Chen, US database systems, for example those provided by Oracle, used to account for nearly 90 percent of China's geographic information, navigation and positioning service market, which posed a serious threat to the country's information construction. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star